The paper deals with the security of communication transmissions, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of encryption and quantum cryptography suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The mention of lossy thermal-noise bosonic channels suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the proof-of-principle experiment suggests that the paper may belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages) as well. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.CR, followed by cs.ET, cs.MM, and cs.PL.
